{"word":"φοίνιος","slug":"φοίνιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φοίνιος</b></el> <el>(φοίνιος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φοινός'><el>φοινός</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>poetic for <a href='S:φόνιος'><el>φόνιος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>when the first <a href='S:syllable'>syll.</a> is to be long, <i>of</i> or <i>like blood, blood-red, red</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>bloody, blood-stained, murderous</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}